<paragraph id="8BE65312237D6056D611FDF0FDB1A767" blockId="5.[55,705,522,898]" box="[55,630,522,547]" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D611FDF0FDB1A767" bold="true" box="[55,630,522,547]" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">
3. Two novelties allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C592891237D6056D775FDF1FDB1A767" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Balkwill &amp; Balkwill" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[339,630,522,546]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Barleria">
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D775FDF1FE0DA767" bold="true" box="[339,458,522,546]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">B. velutina</emphasis>
(sect. 
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D437FDF0FDAAA767" bold="true" box="[529,621,522,546]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">Barleria</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3430099237D6056D45AFDF1FF01A6C7" pageId="5" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE65312237D6056D45AFDF1FF01A6C7" blockId="5.[55,705,522,898]" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">
– 
<taxonomicName id="4C592891237D6056D4B6FDF1FF04A703" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtecta">
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D4B6FDF1FF04A703" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">Barleria obtecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C592891237D6056D7FBFDD4FD93A703" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[477,596,558,582]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D7FBFDD4FD93A703" box="[477,596,558,582]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and pertains to the same section, 
<taxonomicName id="4C592891237D6056D77AFDABFE71A72C" baseAuthorityName="Balkwill &amp; Balkwill" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[348,438,593,617]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D77AFDABFE71A72C" box="[348,438,593,617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">Barleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The same holds for 
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D48CFDABFEE2A7C9" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">B. sceptrum­katanganum</emphasis>
, allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C592891237D6056D7BCFD8FFDD6A7C9" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[410,529,628,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D7BCFD8FFDD6A7C9" box="[410,529,628,652]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its hairiness and the shape of calyces and leaves; it differs by its strongly erect stem which is broader than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C592891237D6056D7E7FD41FDF0A797" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[449,567,698,722]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D7E7FD41FDF0A797" box="[449,567,698,722]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by its leafy spike, the leafy bracts hiding the calyx lobes which are not visible unlike in 
<taxonomicName id="4C592891237D6056D6CBFCFBFEA5A65D" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[237,354,768,792]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D6CBFCFBFEA5A65D" box="[237,354,768,792]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the constant presence of the upper lobes of corolla, which are much larger than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C592891237D6056D611FCBDFF6CA61B" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[55,171,838,862]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F00237D6056D611FCBDFF6CA61B" box="[55,171,838,862]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when present in the latter, and by its considerably larger leaves.
</paragraph>
